      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(heartbeat): remove static iteration cap in seekNextActivePhaseDueMs",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where agents with sub-minute heartbeat intervals and active\nhours would permanently stop running heartbeats when the current time fell\noutside the active window — the static 10,080 iteration cap was calibrated\nfor 1-minute intervals and exhausted too early for shorter intervals.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n**Unified batched seek at >= 30 s step** with backward walk on\ninactive->active transitions:\n\n\\`\\`\\`ts\nconst MIN_SEEK_STEP_MS = 30_000;\nconst multiplier = Math.max(1, Math.ceil(MIN_SEEK_STEP_MS / intervalMs));\nconst batchStepMs = intervalMs * multiplier;\n// … backward walk on prevWasActive===false -> active transition\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n| intervalMs | multiplier | batchStepMs | max iterations | narrow windows |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 60 s+ | 1 | ≤ 60 s | ≤ 10,080 | ✅ per-candidate |\n| 30 s | 1 | 30 s | 20,160 | ✅ per-candidate |\n| 59 s | 1 | 59 s | 10,251 | ✅ per-candidate |\n| 1 s | 30 | 30 s | 20,160 | ✅ 30 s < min window |\n| 500 ms | 60 | 30 s | 20,160 | ✅ backward walk |\n| 1 ms | 30,000 | 30 s | 20,160 | ✅ backward walk |\n\nMax **20,160** production \\`isWithinActiveHours\\` predicate calls\nregardless of intervalMs (~20–200 ms for Intl.DateTimeFormat per call).\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers with sub-minute heartbeat intervals and active hours can correctly\nseek into the next active window. No impact on minute-or-larger intervals\n(multiplier = 1).\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Unit tests (19/19 pass):** 14 existing + 5 new\n- 30s / 09:00-17:00: finds 09:00 next day, phase-aligned\n- **59s / 1min narrow window (09:00-09:01)**: finds 09:00:43 (977 steps)\n- 500ms, startMs active: returns directly (no backward walk)\n- 500ms, inactive->active transition: backward walk finds 09:00:00\n- 1ms / never-active: bounded at 20,160 iter, sub-50ms\n\n**Real behavior proof (\\`node --import tsx\\`, 6 scenarios):**\n\\`\\`\\`\n=== seekNextActivePhaseDueMs v6 (30s unified batch, <= 20,160 calls) ===\n\n1. 30s, 09:00-17:00, start 17:00 -> 09:00:00 next day (active: true)\n2. 59s, 09:00-09:01 window, start 17:00 -> 09:00:43 (steps: 977)\n3. 7s, always-active, start 12:00 -> 12:00 (=startMs)\n4. 1s, never-active, start 12:00 -> 12:00 (elapsed: 0.6ms)\n5. computeNextHeartbeatPhaseDueMs (30s), now 10:00 -> 10:00:30\n6. Full-path: 30s, 20:00->09-17 active -> 09:00:15 next day (active: true)\n\\`\\`\\`\n",
